description:
&lt;p&gt;This locum post is a replacement post while we are looking to appoint a substantive consultant. You will join colleagues in a very dynamic and forward looking Multi-Disciplinary Child and Adolescent Mental Health Service.  The post will be a 10 session post with 8 sessions allocated to the generic S-CAMHS service in Ceredigion and the remaining 2 sessions will be based in Carmarthen to provide consultant time to the HB wide Early Intervention Psychosis Service. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post comes during a period of Health Board-wide service reviews, including a comprehensive reconfiguration of Mental Health, Learning Disabilities and S-CAMHS services within the Health Board.  The aim is to provide a spectrum of flexible and responsive services for the population across the Health Board.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The S-CAMHS is part of the Mental Health &amp; Learning Disabilities Directorate and there has been a significant investment in enhancing existing provision and developing new services across the HDUHB over the last 18 months&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;West Wales is an area of outstanding beauty that offers a variety of outdoor pursuits and beautiful coastline. It is an excellent place to raise a family. Reasonable property prices and excellent state schools contribute to low living costs and a high quality of life.  There are also good road and rail connections to Cardiff and London.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Office accommodation, secretarial support and full IT facilities including access to intranet and internet will be provided.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameDr Warren LloydJob titleClinical Director &amp; Associate Medical Director MH&amp;LD&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email: Warren.Lloyd@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tele: 01267 674130&lt;/p&gt;
